    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a4 Personnel/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-22">May 22,
                            1931</date>.<lb/>[Received May 22—4:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I very greatly appreciate the congratulations you have been good enough to send
                    me on my election as President of the Disarmament Conference. Such encouragement
                    is of particular value to me in the great work which lies before me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
